<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="recognition and notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Recognition and notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea discolor" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the glabrous or subglabrous inflorescence rachis measuring 3.5-11.5 cm long and pedicel 6-16 mm long. It is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. glazioui" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="glazioui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. glazioui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the number and shape of its leaflets; however, individuals of 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. discolor" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not have glandular trichomes and the inflorescence rachis is glabrous or subglabrous, while in 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. glazioui" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="glazioui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. glazioui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they have glandular trichomes and the inflorescence rachis is hirsute or densely so. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea discolor" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. bahiensis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well, although they are differentiated by the characteristics of the leaflets and inflorescences (see &quot;Recognition and notes&quot; section of 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. bahiensis" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, JG" editor="Martius, CFP von" journalOrPublisher="2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="172 - 196" refId="B4" refString="Baker, JG, 1871. Connaraceae. In: Martius, CFP von, Ed., Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt. 2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig: 172 - 196" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt." year="1871">Baker (1871)</bibRefCitation>
indicated only the specimen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Luschnath s. n.</emphasis>
, without mentioning either herbarium, collector number or date. This specimen is deposited in BR and is likely to be the holotype, as no other duplicate has been found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea discolor" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was once treated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aublet" authorityYear="1775" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oxalidaceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Oxalidaceae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Progel, A" journalOrPublisher=") Flora Brasiliensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="473 - 528" refId="B23" refString="Progel, A, 1877. Oxalideae, Geraniaceae, Vivianiaceae. In: Martius CFP von (Ed.) Flora Brasiliensis 12 (2): 473 - 528" title="Oxalideae, Geraniaceae, Vivianiaceae. In: Martius CFP von (Ed." volume="12" year="1877">Progel (1877)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="Progel, 1877" authorityName="Progel" authorityYear="1877" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Eichleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eichleria lucida" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Eichleria lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhlmann, JG" journalOrPublisher="Archivos do Instituto de Biologia Vegetal" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="39 - 40" refId="B16" refString="Kuhlmann, JG, 1934. O genero Eichleria sinonimo de Rourea. Archivos do Instituto de Biologia Vegetal 1: 39 - 40" title="O genero Eichleria sinonimo de Rourea." volume="1" year="1934">Kuhlmann (1934)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the combination of 
<taxonomicName authority="Progel, 1877" authorityName="Progel" authorityYear="1877" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Eichleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eichleria" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Eichleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aublet" authorityYear="1775" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the basionym 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea lucida" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lucida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea lucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
already existed, so he named it as 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. progeliana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="progeliana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. progeliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This name is, however, a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. discolor" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the latter had been published previously (
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, JG" editor="Martius, CFP von" journalOrPublisher="2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="172 - 196" refId="B4" refString="Baker, JG, 1871. Connaraceae. In: Martius, CFP von, Ed., Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt. 2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig: 172 - 196" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt." year="1871">Baker 1871</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
